        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well, I've been sitting on a bunch of a points cause there was nothing of value to spend them on.   So first thing I did when this patch finished, was to dump 12 points into ND.</P><P>Very nice.   Unbuffed added 249 hp to me.</P><P>Here is the unbuffed hp totals for me at each step.</P><P>Base	2499<BR>ND1	2548<BR>ND2	2623<BR>ND3	2748</P><P><BR>All of your items that give you hp and stam are impacted by ND.   HP buffs get no ND modification.  But Stam buffs do get the ND bonus applied to them as well.</P><P>If you divide it out and such, you'll see that the percentage gained at each level does just about exactly match what they say.</P><P>EDIT - sigh.   sig is broken again.  </P><P>EDIT again - ok, think sig is working now.</P><P></P><P><br>-------------------<br><i><b><font color=red><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27731" target="_blank">Urgrim Soulreaper - Warlock</a><br></font id=red></b><BR>Urdral Bloodstorm -  High Priest<br>Urdraco  Dragonsblood - Revenant</i></P><P>Edited by - Urgrim on 08/14/2002  14:33:00<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
